      • getPositionRaw

        public int getPositionRaw()
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        The actual position of the Channel as stored and given by Discord. Role positions are actually based on a pairing of the creation time (as stored in the snowflake id) and the position. If 2 or more roles share the same position then they are sorted based on their creation date. The more recent a role was created, the lower it is in the hierarchy. This is handled by Channel.getPosition() and it is most likely the method you want. If, for some reason, you want the actual position of the Role then this method will give you that value.
        Specified by:
        getPositionRaw in interface Channel
        Returns:
        The true, Discord stored, position of the Channel.
